summary: SummaryDior Addict Lip Glow Butter is a hybrid gloss-balm lip treatment with a buttery texture that provides intense hydration and subtle high-shine color. Available in 5 juicy shades.
details: DetailsBenefitsDior Addict Lip Glow Butter is infused with a peptide and ceramide duo to instantly enhance your lips' appearance.The rich, buttery formula deeply hydrates for 24 hours while visibly smoothing and plumping lips.Discover 5 high-shine, non-sticky colors in 2 finishes - glossy or pearlescent.Research ResultsIn an instrumental test on 30 subjects, Dior Addict Lip Glow Butter visibly smooths and plumps lips, and provides deep hydration for 24 hours.The formula is infused with a peptide and ceramide duo to support the skin barrier for 24 hours.Item 2639603How To UseWear Dior Addict Lip Glow Butter during the day as a hydrating, glossy lip treatment that also adds subtle color to your lips.Apply a thick coat before bed to use as an overnight lip mask for deep hydration.Boost the feeling of hydration and get a "custom" color on your lips by applying over your Dior Addict Lip Glow balm.Ingredients101 Glazed Pink: Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Dimer Dilinoleyl Dimer Dilinoleate, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Methyl Hydrogenated Rosinate, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Squalane, Glyceryl Behenate/Eicosadioate, C12-15 Alkyl Benzoate, Stearalkonium Hectorite, Parfum (Fragrance), 1,2-Hexanediol, Propylene Carbonate, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Hydroxystearic Acid, Tribehenin, Ethyl Vanillin, Menthol, Prunus Avium (Sweet Cherry) Seed Oil, Ammonium Glycyrrhizate, Ceramide Ng, Stearic Acid, Peg-10 Phytosterol, Tocopherol, Mentha Piperita (Peppermint) Oil, Vanillin, Lactic Acid, Trimethylolpropane Triisostearate, Anethole, Beta-Caryophyllene, Pinene, Limonene, Terpineol, Tin Oxide, Palmitoyl Hexapeptide-12, Propyl Gallate. May Contain: CI 77891 (Titanium Dioxide), CI 45410 (Red 28 Lake), CI 77492 (Iron Oxides).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Wear Dior Addict Lip Glow Butter during the day as a hydrating, glossy lip treatment that also adds subtle color to your lips.Apply a thick coat before bed to use as an overnight lip mask for deep hydration.Boost the feeling of hydration and get a "custom" color on your lips by applying over your Dior Addict Lip Glow balm.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I got the DIOR Addict Lip Glow Butter - shade 105 Lychee, which is described as a luminous fuchsia, and it did not disappoint. It's described as a hybrid gloss-balm, and honestly, that's exactly what it feels like.

Let's talk about the packaging first. It's exactly what you'd expect from Dior ‚Äì sleek, elegant, and feels luxurious in hand. The tube is sturdy, and it has a beautiful, minimalist design that feels very high-end. There's also a cute little "Dior" logo charm attached, which is a nice touch and adds to the overall premium feel. It's definitely something you wouldn't mind pulling out of your bag for a touch-up.

When you apply it, the first thing you notice is the buttery texture. It glides on incredibly smoothly, feeling rich and luxurious on the lips without being sticky or heavy. It's truly a pleasure to apply. As for the scent, it's very subtle ‚Äì a delicate, almost sweet and lightly vanilla-esque fragrance that isn't overpowering or artificial. It fades quickly after application, which is great if you're sensitive to scented lip products.

The 105 Lychee shade is stunning ‚Äì it gives my lips a vibrant yet subtle luminous fuchsia tint with a gorgeous, glossy finish. It makes my lips look healthier, fuller, and adds a beautiful pop of color without being overwhelming.

What really impressed me are the benefits. This isn't just a pretty gloss; it's genuinely hydrating. My lips feel intensely moisturized, and that hydration really does seem to last for hours. The formula is infused with a peptide and ceramide duo, which I think contributes to the visible smoothing and plumping effect. My lips definitely look smoother and more plump after application, which is a big win.

Now, for the price ‚Äì these are definitely a luxury item, typically retailing around $42. Yes, it's an investment for a lip product, but for the luxurious feel, effective results, and the gorgeous shade, I think it's absolutely worth it if you're looking for a high-quality, hydrating lip product that brings a bit of luxury into your everyday routine.
I've been wearing it on its own for a quick touch of color and hydration, and it's perfect for that effortless, "my lips but better, but with a pop of fuchsia" look. It also wears really comfortably throughout the day.
faceoff_positive.headline: Lovely color

faceoff_negative.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] As someone who's a fan of Dior's beauty line, I had high hopes for the Lip Glow Butter in Glazed Pink‚Äîbut unfortunately, this one missed the mark for me.

Let's start with the packaging. At first glance, it's cute and eye-catching, especially with the little Dior charm attached. That detail actually ended up being my favorite part‚ÄîI can totally see myself repurposing it as a charm for a keychain or bag once the product is used up. However, the rest of the packaging feels incredibly light and flimsy, almost toy-like. It doesn't have that weighty, luxe feel you'd expect from a Dior lip product, especially given the high price point.

Speaking of price, for what you pay, the amount of product is shockingly small. See photo of sized comparison too. The tube itself feels hollow‚Äînot fully filled‚Äîand it gives the impression that you're paying more for the name than the substance. If you're looking for value, this really isn't it.

On the plus side, the texture is smooth and buttery, as the name implies. It glides on effortlessly and gives a sheer wash of glazed pink that's flattering and easy to wear. It's comfortable, non-sticky, and does a decent job at keeping lips moisturized throughout the day. The scent is a light, sweet vanilla with a hint of fruity candy‚Äîpleasant and not overpowering.

As for the ingredients, it includes shea butter and cherry oil, which give it that nourishing feel, but I'd say it's more of a light hydrator than a deep treatment balm. Ideal for touch-ups or layering over other products, but not something I'd rely on for truly dry lips.

In short: aesthetically it's adorable, and I do enjoy the actual formula. But the cheap-feeling packaging, tiny size, and overall lack of value really detract from the experience. You're mostly paying for the branding and that charming Dior trinket‚Äînot for a product that feels or performs like a true luxury item.
faceoff_negative.headline: Super cute and trendy BUT not worth it!
